.TH IMGSIZE "6D" "May 5, 2004" "IRIX 6.5
.SH NAME
imgsize - print the size of an image
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBimgsize\fP \fBinimage\fP \fB[-2]\fP
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fIimgsize\fP prints the xsize, ysize, and zsize of the named image. If the -2
option is given, only the xsize and ysize are printed. This is useful in
shell scripts that perform a sequence of image processing operations.
.SH SEE ALSO
istat(6D)
